@node INTRO "Introduction"
 AmigaNCP-Backup provides a possiblity to perform incremental ba	ckups of your
Psion. Incremental backup means that no blind copy is performed. Original and
backup are compared first, and then only changed files are copied. This makes
backup procedure incredibly faster.
 Unlike PC Backup program supplied with PsiWin or EPOC Connect this program
does not leave on your Psion any additional data (like PsiWin.ini file) and
does not depend on machine-specific data (like machine ID), it stores backups
in a user-defined drawer. This makes it possible to have several backups of
the same machine.
 @{"Author" LINK "AUTHOR"} hopes you'll like this program.
@endnode
@node Installation
 Installation of this program is simple. Just double click on "Install" icon
and follow the instructions. The installer will place the program into
AmigaNCP's drawer. The program itself will be placed in "Tools" drawer and
its documentation (this file) - in "Docs" drawer. If you will install a
source code it will be placed in "Source/AmigaNCP-Backup" drawer.
@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"
 To use this program you need:
 
 - AmigaOS v2.1 or better;
 - MUI user interfa	ce library v3.6 or better;
 - AmigaNCP any version;
 - The following MUI custom classes:
   - LEDGauge.mcc;
   - Infotext.mcc;
   - NListview.mcc and NList.mcc.

 All these components can be found on Aminet. MUI custom classes
are included in the archive.

 Also you will need a stack at least 16384 bytes long. Note that
AmigaNCP-Backup does not set up a new stack for itself, it relies on existing
one. If you start the program from Workbench, do not worry about that, this
value is already specified in the "Stack size" parameter of the icon. But if
you run it from CLI, you should take care about it. But in general this is
also not a problem because many modern CLI software (especially software
ported from UNIX) require a large stack too, so if you are CLI user you
should just place "Stack xxxxxx" command into your User-Startup file and
forget about this problem. For example, on my system i use 102400 bytes
(100 kb) for CLI stack.

